    <!-- Settings Descriptions -->
    <string name="desc_max_risk_per_trade">The maximum percentage of your total account equity you are willing to lose on a single trade. If your stop loss is hit, you will lose exactly this amount.</string>
    <string name="desc_max_open_exposure">The maximum combined risk across all your currently open trades. This protects your account from sudden, broad market crashes.</string>
    <string name="desc_max_portfolio_allocation">The maximum percentage of your total account capital that can be invested in a single stock. Prevents you from putting all your eggs in one basket.</string>
    <string name="desc_min_risk_reward">The minimum ratio between your potential profit (Reward) and potential loss (Risk) required to take a trade. A ratio of 2.0 means you expect to make twice as much as you risk losing.</string>

    <!-- Education - 5 Layers -->
    <string name="title_education_concept">TradingMate Concept: The 5 Layers</string>
    <string name="edu_5_layers_intro">Our system evaluates stocks through 5 distinct \"Layers\" of analysis. A stock must pass the earlier layers before the later layers matter. We use these tags to quickly identify the current state of a stock.</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_1_title">Layer 1: QUAL (Quality/Fundamentals)</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_1_content" formatted="false">The foundation. Does the company make money? We look for ROE > 15%, Net Profit Margin > 10%, consistent 3Y profit growth, and low debt (D/E &lt; 1.5).</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_2_title">Layer 2: VAL (Valuation)</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_2_content">Is the price fair? Even a great company is a bad investment if you pay too much. We compare Current P/E to Historical P/E and check Price-to-Book ratios.</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_3_title">Layer 3: DIV (Dividend)</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_3_content" formatted="false">For income investors. We accumulate and compound high-yield stocks (&gt; 5%) indefinitely. Keep holding and reinvesting dividends unless fundamentals break (ROE &lt; 15% or high debt) or the dividend yield drops below 3%.</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_4_title">Layer 4: MOM (Momentum)</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_4_content">Are buyers stepping in? We use MACD crossovers and moving averages to confirm that the trend has actually shifted to the upside. Never catch a falling knife.</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_5_title">Layer 5: SUP (Support/Technicals)</string>
    <string name="edu_layer_5_content">The trigger. We use RSI (Relative Strength Index) to find when prices are \'oversold\' (RSI &lt; 35) at major support levels, providing a low-risk entry point.</string>
